    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it doesn't feel temporary. it feels permanent. like the spark is just... gone. i keep waiting to feel alive again, but that version of me is dead and buried. i'm just the leftovers. does it even make sense to keep dragging these remains around if there's nothing left inside?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
